                    <strong><font size="+1" color="#800000">&nbsp;REST OF TODAY</font></strong>
                    &nbsp;West winds 15 to 25 kt increasing to 30 kt by
                    &nbsp;midday, then becoming northwest gales to 35 kt this afternoon.
                    &nbsp;Showers. Waves 2 to 4 ft building to 3 to 6 ft occasionally to 8
                    &nbsp;ft.

                    <strong><font size="+1" color="#800000">&nbsp;TONIGHT</font></strong>
                    &nbsp;Northwest gales to 35 kt becoming west to 30 kt after
                    &nbsp;midnight. Chance of showers in the evening. Waves 3 to 6 ft
                    &nbsp;occasionally to 8 ft.

                    <strong><font size="+1" color="#800000">&nbsp;WEDNESDAY</font></strong>
                    &nbsp;West winds 15 to 20 kt becoming northwest 10 to 15
                    &nbsp;kt in the afternoon. Slight chance of showers in the morning.
                    &nbsp;Waves 2 to 4 ft subsiding to 1 to 3 ft in the afternoon.

                    <strong><font size="+1" color="#800000">&nbsp;WEDNESDAY NIGHT</font></strong>
                    &nbsp;Northwest winds 5 to 10 kt becoming southwest
                    &nbsp;after midnight. Partly cloudy. Waves around 1 ft.
